{"lemma":"عَنْزِ","slug":"عَنْزِ","root":"ع.ن.ز","root_slug":"ع-ن-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30744","n30747","n30748"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goat, goats","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"female goat, she-goat, nanny goat","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʕVnz- (“goat”). Cognate with Hebrew עֵז (éz)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30744","headword_ar":"عَنَزَ","root":"Enz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozN","text_ar":"عَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwzN","text_ar":"عُنُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed, went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retired to a distance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA;) and thus ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtnz","text_ar":"اعتنز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies; (S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEnz","text_ar":"استعنز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) or these two verbs, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEn~z","text_ar":"تعنّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed, went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retired to a distance, from the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtnz","text_ar":"اعتنز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he alighted in a place aside"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from others"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotanizN","text_ar":"مُعْتَنِزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanazahu","text_ar":"عَنَزَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanazuwhu","text_ar":"عَنَزُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozN","text_ar":"عَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pierced him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust him, with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanazap","text_ar":"عَنَزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they pierced him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanazapN","text_ar":"عَنَزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA","IKtt","A"]},{"entry_id":"n30747","headword_ar":"عَنْزٌ","root":"Enz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-goat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female of the common goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-goat a year old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozapN","text_ar":"عَنْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Freytag, from the Kitáb el-Addád:)] and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female of the mountain-goat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the gazelle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonuzN","text_ar":"اَعْنُزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwzN","text_ar":"عُنُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAzN","text_ar":"عِنَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord, to some, the last of these is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozN","text_ar":"عَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the last of the senses expl. above. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA karukobataYi AlEanozi","text_ar":"هُمَا كَرُكْبَتَىِ العَنْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are like the two knees of the she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov. applied to two men vying with each other, (O, K,) or equalling each other, (TA,) because her two knees, when she desires to lie down, fall together. (O, K. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 861: where, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEnz","text_ar":"العنز"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus I find in a MS. copy of the Proverbs of Meyd.]) And it is said in another prov., to him who commits a crime that occasions his destruction,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taku kaA@loEanozi taboHavu Eani Almudoyapi","text_ar":"لَا تَكُ كَا@لْعَنْزِ تَبْحَثُ عَنِ المُدْيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Be not thou like the she-goat that scrapes up the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, from over the butcher's knife"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAHivN","text_ar":"بَاحِثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayawomi AlEanozi","text_ar":"كَيَوْمِ العَنْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day like the day of the she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; mentioned by Th; alluding to its bringing death. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiYa yawoma AlEanozi","text_ar":"لَقِىَ يَوْمَ العَنْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He met with the day of the she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is also a prov., (O, TA,) applied to him who meets with that which destroys him, (O, K,) or to him who labours for his own destruction. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanozu","text_ar":"العَنْزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ε","text_ar":"ε","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the left"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or (as some figure the constellation)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elbow of Auriga:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEinaAzu","text_ar":"العِنَازُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ζ","text_ar":"ζ","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"η","text_ar":"η","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the left"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrist together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEay~uwq","text_ar":"العَيُّوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Capella"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kzw in his description of Auriga.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female eagle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanosN","text_ar":"عَنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwzN","text_ar":"عُنُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female vulture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwzN","text_ar":"عُنُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrd, O.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species of bustard called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubAraY","text_ar":"حُبارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, K) is sometimes thus termed: (O:) and it is said to be also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanozapu","text_ar":"العَنْزَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female of the hawk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of aquatic bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K; *) [by some, in the present day, applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gray heron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanozu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَنْزُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of fish; also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozuAlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَنْزُالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, O:) accord. to Ibn- 'Abbád, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain great fish, which a mule can hardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nowise, carry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) and the pl., he says, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonizapN","text_ar":"اَعْنِزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozN","text_ar":"عَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hill, such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamap","text_ar":"اَكَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a black"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamap","text_ar":"اَكَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rock in the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwzN","text_ar":"عُنُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land having in it ruggedness and sand and stones and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the species of tamarisk called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avol","text_ar":"اَثْل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilN","text_ar":"بَاطِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","IDrd","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n30748","headword_ar":"عَنْزٌ","root":"Enz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see its n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanazapN","text_ar":"عَنَزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}